-- American Axle posts quarterly loss after charges
-- 
-- Fri Feb 2, 2007 8:14am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/02/us-americanaxle-results-idUSWEN348020070202

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings Inc. ( AXL.N ) posted a quarterly net loss on Friday as it took charges for worker buyouts and idling U.S. manufacturing capacity for parts for mid-size light trucks. 


 American Axle reported a net loss of $188.6 million, or $3.74 per share, for its fourth quarter, compared with net income of $4.5 million, or 9 cents per share, a year earlier. Revenue fell 8.4 percent to $781.1 million.